	<section class="fluid-container category-news-items clearfix">
		<div class="row">
			<div class="category-news-items-wrapper col-lg-9">
				<div class="clearfix">
											<div class="news-item news-category-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
																							   																									
							<a href="../understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-arkansas" class="title">
								Medical Marijuana and Laws in Arkansas
							</a>

															<div class="thumb">
									<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(../../files/7a0c03c1108aa83286a28132e18cfdd61b4140f9.jpg);"></div>
								</div>
							
							<div class="source">
															</div>

							<div class="text">
								<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Arkansas passed a law to legalize medical cannabis in 2016 through a ballot measure that received 53.2% of the state’s vote. The law allows qualifying patients to&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">purchase 3 ounces of medical marijuana per 14-day period</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">.&nbsp;</span><br></p>
							</div>

							<a href="../understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-arkansas" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
						</div>
											<div class="news-item news-category-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
																							   																									
							<a href="../understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-arizona" class="title">
								Arizona Medical Marijuana Laws Explained
							</a>

															<div class="thumb">
									<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(../../files/6216c62defaf998689d4708a4684f899767d3066.jpg);"></div>
								</div>
							
							<div class="source">
															</div>

							<div class="text">
								<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Arizona passed a law to legalize medical cannabis in 2010 through Proposition 203 that received 50.13% of the state’s vote. The law allows qualifying patients to possess&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">2.5 ounces of medical marijuana and to grow up to 12 plants</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">.</span><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(112, 87, 75);">&nbsp;</span><br></p>
							</div>

							<a href="../understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-arizona" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
						</div>
											<div class="news-item news-category-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
																							   																									
							<a href="../understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-alaska" class="title">
								Understanding Laws on Medical Cannabis in Alaska
							</a>

															<div class="thumb">
									<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(../../files/a282a1d9bfd0eed37b25aa6a3b9199aa1a5bf892.jpg);"></div>
								</div>
							
							<div class="source">
															</div>

							<div class="text">
								<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Alaska passed a law to&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">legalize medical cannabis in 1998&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">through a ballot measure that received 58% of the state’s vote. The law allows qualifying patients to possess 1 ounce of medical marijuana and to grow up to 6 plants, only 3 of which can be mature.</span><br></p>
							</div>

							<a href="../understanding-medical-cannabis-laws-in-alaska" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
						</div>
											<div class="news-item news-category-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
																							   																									
							<a href="../5-important-considerations-for-patients-using-medical-cannabis" class="title">
								5 Important Considerations for Patients Using Medical Cannabis
							</a>

															<div class="thumb">
									<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(../../files/a2d8ed1c340bd93fff33eccc9305ac6dad995c00.jpg);"></div>
								</div>
							
							<div class="source">
															</div>

							<div class="text">
								<p><span style="color: rgb(112, 87, 75); font-size: 16px;">There been a clear resurgence in interest in cannabis, more commonly called marijuana, as medicine. The federal government made cannabis use illegal in 1970 with passage of the Comprehensive Drug Abuse Prevention and Control Act</span><br></p>
							</div>

							<a href="../5-important-considerations-for-patients-using-medical-cannabis" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
						</div>
											<div class="news-item news-category-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
																							   																									
							<a href="../5-reasons-to-legalize-medical-cannabis-nationally" class="title">
								5 Reasons to Legalize Medical Cannabis Nationally
							</a>

															<div class="thumb">
									<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(../../files/8ea8fbf393a993ce01a07c65ba2f3db21af89d3c.jpg);"></div>
								</div>
							
							<div class="source">
															</div>

							<div class="text">
								<p><span style="color: rgb(112, 87, 75); font-size: 16px;">Medical marijuana, or cannabis, was made illegal by the Controlled Substances Act of 1970. This act classified marijuana as a Schedule 1 drug indicating that it was highly addictive and had no medicinal value.</span><br></p>
							</div>

							<a href="../5-reasons-to-legalize-medical-cannabis-nationally" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
						</div>
											<div class="news-item news-category-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
																							   																									
							<a href="../4-reasons-doctors-are-reluctant-to-prescribe-medical-cannabis" class="title">
								4 Reasons Doctors are Reluctant to Prescribe Medical Cannabis
							</a>

															<div class="thumb">
									<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(../../files/e9ba1313c60973369b50678ab7c0eff562a52b53.jpg);"></div>
								</div>
							
							<div class="source">
															</div>

							<div class="text">
								<p><span style="color: rgb(112, 87, 75); font-size: 16px;">Too few doctors recommending medical cannabis remains the primary obstacle faced by patients with qualifying medical conditions in states where it has been legalized. There is data available, and more accumulating every day, that marijuana is effective as a treatment for several medical conditions and symptoms.</span><br></p>
							</div>

							<a href="../4-reasons-doctors-are-reluctant-to-prescribe-medical-cannabis" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
						</div>
											<div class="news-item news-category-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
																							   																									
							<a href="../8-common-medical-conditions-considered-treatable-with-medical-cannabis" class="title">
								8 Common Medical Conditions Considered Treatable with Medical Cannabis
							</a>

															<div class="thumb">
									<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(../../files/6d6d683d53f1978b130b85a850780d29889e54bf.jpg);"></div>
								</div>
							
							<div class="source">
															</div>

							<div class="text">
								<p><span style="color: rgb(112, 87, 75); font-size: 16px;">Surprisingly cannabis has been used medically for over 5000 years and physicians in the United States were prescribing cannabis as early as 1850 for treating ailments such as nerve pain, alcoholism, opiate addiction, and seizures.&nbsp;</span><br></p>
							</div>

							<a href="../8-common-medical-conditions-considered-treatable-with-medical-cannabis" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
						</div>
											<div class="news-item news-category-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
																							   																									
							<a href="../4-surprising-facts-about-medical-cannabis" class="title">
								4 Surprising Facts About Medical Cannabis
							</a>

															<div class="thumb">
									<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(../../files/37d5547d89952116a25057ec8fa8330864e2a0c5.jpg);"></div>
								</div>
							
							<div class="source">
															</div>

							<div class="text">
								<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">You may have guessed that marijuana, or cannabis, is the most commonly used illegal drug in America. Surprisingly </span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">cannabis has been used medically for over 5000 years</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"> and physicians in the United States were prescribing cannabis in 1850 for the treatment of ailments such as nerve pain, alcoholism, opiate addiction, and seizures.</span><br></p>
							</div>

							<a href="../4-surprising-facts-about-medical-cannabis" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
						</div>
											<div class="news-item news-category-news-item news-item-cell col-lg-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
																							   																									
							<a href="../what-is-cannabis-or-marijuana" class="title">
								What is Cannabis or Marijuana?
							</a>

															<div class="thumb">
									<div class="bg-thumb" style="background-image: url(../../files/b19015890a27b1df0efc0f014bda9496c51ce44b.jpg);"></div>
								</div>
							
							<div class="source">
															</div>

							<div class="text">
								<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">It’s hard to believe that cannabis, also known as marijuana, has been used medically for over 5000 years. Physicians in the United States prescribed cannabis as early as 1850 for&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">treating ailments such as nerve pain, alcoholism, opiate addiction, and seizures</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">.&nbsp;</span><br></p>
							</div>

							<a href="../what-is-cannabis-or-marijuana" class="read-more">Continue Reading</a>
